I think what he meant here was to render sequentially, not 
simultaneously.  On my last project I had four or five seperate 
'projects', each needed 190 frames rendered, which took only a few hours 
each.  It would have been much more convenient to have Imagine 
automatically start the next one after finishing.  As it is, I have to 
