>Don DeCosta writes:
>
>> What do you think would happen if you ran multiple instances of Imagine
>> BUT you gave them each a lower priority than the previous?
>Yes, but they will all allocate memory at the start of the rendering
>that means you will need memory that can hold all of them at the same
