I'm pretty darned sure that with an Imagine Project rendering at PRI 0,
the Imagine Project at PRI -10 will never get enough CPU cycles to
allocate any memory for objects until the PRI 0 job ends, so you'd only
need enough memory to hold multiple copies of the Project Editor.

