Not really... usually AREXX ports allow you commands that mimic menu items
or other procedures for which routines already exist in the program.  Once
the port is in place, adding more commands is easy (unless you add completely
new functionality... unlikely!).  One more .c file could implement the AREXX
port, with perhaps some minor changes in other files (#ifdef _AMIGA_...).

