@node IML-169 " MSG-169  Subject: Re: Making a room"

Subject: Re: Making a room
Date: Wed, 20 Jul 94 9:29:59 CDT
From: johnh@merle.acns.nwu.edu

> 
> 
> 	What is the best (good) way to make a room,... i.e. the floor,
> walls, ceiling.  Can you just make a box, scale it big and set up lights
> and stuff inside?  Also, there doesn't seem to be a _box_ primitive!?!? 
> 
	Actually, there _is_ a box primitive, but it is called a
CYLINDER.  In the requester, just specify 4 points for your circumference
and, voila, a box, with or without top and bottom.  If you're fussy,
you can realign the axes so they are perpendicular to the sides of
the box.


