@node IML-193 " MSG-193  Subject: Making a room"

Subject: Making a room
Date: Thu, 21 Jul 94 02:40:00 -0100
From: torgeir.holm@tbc.powertech.no (Torgeir Holm)

>>  What is the best (good) way to make a room,... i.e. the floor,
>> walls, ceiling.  Can you just make a box, scale it big and set up lig
>> and stuff inside?  Also, there doesn't seem to be a _box_ primitive!?
>>
>>  Ed

>Try a tube with four sides.

Try a primitive plane with 1 section each way, which you extrude to your
desired length. This gives you more precise control over the size of the
finished object.

When you work with the Primitive tube you have to rotate the axis to get
the bounding box right, and you will have to do some calculating to get
the size precize.


