Real3D has AREXX support in the amiga version, but not in the Windows
version. It doesn't seem like Realsoft doubted the value of adding it
for the amiga version. Still the project files are fully iterchangable
and the programs are almost identical.

I think impulse shold do the same. The amiga version would improve a lot
if it had an AREXX port. The ability to communicate directly with ADpro
for converting rendered frames into an anim would be great. Of course
this can be done with Sentry, unless you use flares or haze.

Denying 90% of the imagine users an Arexx port because the other 10%
can't have it seems a bit strange IMHO.



