This is, unfortunately, a violation of the terms of both the CIS and the AOL 
usage agreements, as well as the copyrights that each service holds to the 
compilation of messages posted to the various forums. CIS in particular is 
*very* agressive about pursuing people who violate this section of the usage 
agreement.

So no, you can't do that. Unless you *want* an expensive and 
difficult-to-win lawsuit on your hands. :)
