@node IML-281 " MSG-281  Subject: TDDD format, 3ds"

Subject: TDDD format, 3ds
Date: Mon, 25 Jul 94 08:02:00 -0100
From: torgeir.holm@tbc.powertech.no (Torgeir Holm)

>I just got the book _Inside_3D_Studio_3.0_ and it has lots of
>good stuff on it... textures, etc.  Can I convert the .3ds files for us
>with Imagine?

Yes, I use InterChange, by Syndesis Corporation, to convert files
3dStudio <- > Imagine. It works great, and is available for both Amiga,
PC and I think SGI. It supports a lot of different formats.

>Also, I picked up TDDD.specs on the net somewhere and was
>wondering if it is the current spec.  Says it's by Steve Worley.  Are
>there several revisions of the spec?

